x;"><strong>Is the turmoil in the department store world benefiting RTR? Ar=
e brands now
relying more on RTR than on multi-brand retail chains?=C2=A0</strong></p><p=
 style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">Tru=
st is everything in this industry, and I=E2=80=99m sure that we benefited f=
rom the fact that there=E2=80=99s just a lot of chaos in the industry and w=
e=E2=80=99ve been this trusted partner for over 15 years. And you could rea=
lly deliver one of two things to a brand. You could deliver huge sales numb=
ers, which with some of our brands, we do. But the second thing you could
deliver is customer acquisition. Given the constant fluctuations they=E2=80=
=99ve had to experience over the last few years=E2=80=94with everything rel=
ated to Farfetch and Matches, and now what=E2=80=99s happening with departm=
ent stores=E2=80=94brands have had to put more pressure, in many cases, on =
their D.T.C. businesses.<br/><br/>Fundamentally, Rent the Runway has brough=
t the traditional retail store into someone=E2=80=99s home. We make it real=
ly easy for the customer to try things risk-free=E2=80=94the average custom=
er is now trying over 50
brands a year from us. She has an organic experience wearing the brand, whi=
ch we know is critical for a lot of these brands.<br/><br/><strong>What=E2=
=80=99s the value prop for brands to partner with Rent the Runway?</strong>=
<br/><br/>I think the analogy here is actually Sephora. This is what I aspi=
re to be. Seven or eight years ago, Sephora changed their strategy from hav=
ing all of the blockbuster brands on their platform to one where they were =
going to showcase indie brands and ensure that they were a
discovery engine for beauty, so that people come into that store multiple t=
imes a week, whether online or in person. We=E2=80=99ve become this entirel=
y new marketing channel for coveted brands to acquire future customers of a=
ll ages, and I think the brands are seeing this in their data. So the hotte=
st brands in the world are coming to us now because they see us as a market=
ing opportunity, and a place where customers can really find the latest and=
 greatest in designer fashion in constant rotation.</p>
